<task id="014" project="email-communication-solution-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>AttachmentList sub-component framework + client-side cap enforcement</title>
    <phase>Wave 1 — Engine + Wrappers + Sub-Components</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>5</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>011</dependencies>
    <blocks>015, 016, 017, 018, 020, 028</blocks>
    <tags>react, frontend, fluent-ui, communication</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Cap enforcement (NFR-04: 150 attachments / 35 MB / warn at 25 MB) is a load-bearing client-side gate; ADR-021 (Fluent v9) styling; impacts every email sent. FULL guards against regressions across all 4 sources (015-018).</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>C</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <fr-refs>FR-07</fr-refs>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the `<AttachmentList />` framework component at `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.tsx` — this task handles the UNIFIED list + cap enforcement. Source-specific pickers (`LocalAttachmentSource`, `SpeAttachmentSource`, `RelatedRecordAttachmentSource`, `WizardAttachmentSource`) ship in parallel tasks 015-018.

    Framework requirements (FR-07):
    - Renders attachments in a single unified list (DESPITE coming from 4 different sources)
    - Each row: filename / size / source badge (`local` / `spe` / `related` / `wizard`) / remove-X button
    - Cap enforcement (NFR-04):
      * Hard block at 150 attachments — disable Add buttons, surface validation error
      * Hard block at 35 MB total size — same
      * Soft warning at 25 MB — show inline warning banner ("Attachments approaching cap")
    - Renders source-picker buttons in order from `attachmentSources` prop:
      `attachmentSources: IComposerAttachmentSource[]` — engine passes through what the wrapper/host configures (e.g., a SendEmailStep in a Matter wizard might enable `['local', 'spe', 'related']`)
    - Each picker button on click opens the relevant source component (built in 015-018; this task wires the buttons but the source components are stubs)
    - Component is CONTROLLED: receives `attachments: IAttachment[]`, `onChange(IAttachment[])` from engine reducer

    `IAttachment` shape (define in `AttachmentList.types.ts`):
    ```
    {
      id: string;             // local UUID for list operations
      name: string;
      sizeBytes: number;
      mimeType: string;
      source: 'local' | 'spe' | 'related' | 'wizard';
      driveItemId?: string;   // canonical for non-local sources (FR-21)
      localFile?: File;       // for 'local' source only — uploaded at send time
    }
    ```

    Files:
    - `subcomponents/AttachmentList.tsx` (NEW)
    - `subcomponents/AttachmentList.types.ts` (NEW)
    - `subcomponents/sources/` dir scaffolded (NEW) — pickers added in 015-018
    - Update `EmailComposer.types.ts` — re-export `IAttachment`
    - Update `EmailComposer/index.ts` — export `AttachmentList`, `IAttachment`
    - Wire into engine `AttachmentsRegion` slot in `EmailComposer.tsx`
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React + Fluent UI v9 developer comfortable with controlled list components + size formatting + Fluent `Toolbar` / `Card` / `MessageBar` primitives.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `<AttachmentList />` compiles + lint-clean; renders a unified list with source badges + remove buttons; enforces 150-count + 35-MB-total hard caps with disabled Add buttons; shows 25 MB warning banner. Source-picker button slots present for each `attachmentSources` entry (clicking does nothing yet — pickers ship in 015-018). Bundle clean.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-07: 4 sources, unified list, source badge, server-enforced caps (existing in `CommunicationService.cs`). Client warns at 25 MB / blocks at 35 MB / 150 — these are duplicated client-side to surface UX before the user hits send.

      `driveItemId` is the canonical attachment reference per FR-21 (Wave 0). Non-local sources resolve to a driveItemId; local source uploads at send time and the server captures the resulting driveItem. This component just carries the structured data; the `send()` flow in the engine uses these IDs.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.tsx (NEW)</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/EmailComposer/subcomponents/AttachmentList.types.ts (NEW)</file>
