  <steps>
    <step order="1">Create `subcomponents/sources/` directory (empty — 015-018 fill in).</step>
    <step order="2">Author `AttachmentList.types.ts` with `IAttachment` shape per prompt.</step>
    <step order="3">Author `AttachmentList.tsx`:
      - Props: `{ attachments: IAttachment[]; onChange: (next: IAttachment[]) =&gt; void; attachmentSources: IComposerAttachmentSource[]; onValidationError?: (field: 'attachments', code: string, message: string) =&gt; void; wizardContext?: unknown; relatedRecord?: { entityName: string; recordId: string } }`
      - Compute `totalBytes = attachments.reduce((s, a) =&gt; s + a.sizeBytes, 0)`
      - Compute caps: `atCountCap = attachments.length &gt;= 150`, `atSizeCap = totalBytes &gt;= 35 * 1024 * 1024`, `atWarning = totalBytes &gt;= 25 * 1024 * 1024`
      - On cap breach, dispatch validation error via `onValidationError`
      - Render:
        * Toolbar with one button per `attachmentSources` entry — `Add from {source}` — disabled when `atCountCap` or `atSizeCap`; onClick stub (sources fill in 015-018 via a registry/dispatch mechanism)
        * `&lt;MessageBar intent="warning"&gt;` shown when `atWarning &amp;&amp; !atSizeCap` — text "Attachments approaching 35 MB cap"
        * `&lt;MessageBar intent="error"&gt;` shown when `atSizeCap` — text "Attachment size cap reached"
        * Each attachment row: filename, formatted size (`formatBytes(n)`), source badge `&lt;Tag&gt;`, remove button</step>
    <step order="4">Inline `formatBytes(n: number): string` util — handles B/KB/MB/GB.</step>
    <step order="5">Wire into engine's `AttachmentsRegion` slot — engine passes attachmentSources + wizardContext + relatedRecord through.</step>
    <step order="6">Update `EmailComposer.types.ts` re-export + `EmailComposer/index.ts` barrel.</step>
    <step order="7">Smoke test in dev: add stub attachments at various sizes; verify count cap at 150, size cap at 35 MB, warning at 25 MB.</step>
    <step order="8">Run `npm run build` + `npm run lint` clean.</step>
    <step order="8.5">Step 9.5 quality gates — code-review + adr-check.</step>
    <step order="9">Update `TASK-INDEX.md`: 014 ✅.</step>
    <step order="10">Update `current-task.md` per task-execute protocol.</step>
  </steps>

